Here is an example prompt to generate a graphQL query: 
Get all tokens held by vitalik.eth on Ethereum

query getAllTokensBy {
  TokenBalances(input: {filter: { owner: {_eq: "vitalik.eth"}}, limit: 10, blockchain: ethereum}) {
    TokenBalance {
      amount
      chainId
      id
      lastUpdatedBlock
      lastUpdatedTimestamp
      owner {
        addresses
      }
      tokenAddress
      tokenId
      token {
        name
        symbol
      }
    }
  }
}

Here is an example prompt to generate a graphQL query: 
Get all the token holders and their ENS names for Tether

query GetTokenBalances {
  TokenBalances(
    input: {blockchain: ethereum, limit: 10, filter: {tokenAddress: {_eq: "0xdac17f958d2ee523a2206206994597c13d831ec7"}}}
  ) {
    TokenBalance {
      amount
      chainId
      owner {
        addresses
        domains {
          id
          name
          owner
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

